pydoc-info
==========

pydoc-info is an Emacs package for searching and browsing Python
documentation in the Info browser.

It enables you to quickly find the relevant documentation using the
standard command `info-lookup-symbol'.


Setup and install
-----------------

Before using this package, you may need to download and install the
Python documentation in the Info format.

    wget <...>
    sudo cp python.info /usr/share/info
    sudo install-info --info-dir=/usr/share/info python.info


Then add the following to your ~/.emacs.d/init.el.

    (add-to-list 'load-path "~/path/to/pydoc-info")
    (require 'pydoc-info)
